In this article, President Barack Obama sends a letter to the Speaker of the House of Representatives and the President of the Senate regarding the annual renewal of the Cuba emergency. He states that Section 202(d) of the National Emergencies Act requires the President to publish a notice in the Federal Register and transmit it to Congress prior to the anniversary date of the declaration in order to continue the national emergency. The emergency in question pertains to the Government of Cuba's destruction of two unarmed U.S.-registered civilian aircraft in international airspace north of Cuba on February 24, 1996. Obama confirms that he has sent the notice to the Federal Register, stating that the national emergency is to continue beyond March 1, 2011.